## (D) CROSS-SOURCE SYNTHESIS

### 1. Product Feature Claims Without Wikipedia Backing or Contradicting Wikipedia

| # | Product URL | Feature Claim | Wikipedia URL | Contradiction |
|---|-------------|---------------|---------------|---------------|
| 1 | [Thunder Group Saute Pan](http://localhost:7770/thunder-group-saute-pan-7-quart.html) | Claims "avoids gassing" as a common occurrence on burners | [Sautéing](http://localhost:8090/content/wikipedia_en_all_nopic/A/Sauteing) | Wikipedia does not mention "gassing" as a common cooking phenomenon; the term appears to be a marketing fabrication |
| 2 | [Ivation Ceramic Cookware Set](http://localhost:7770/ivation-ceramic-cookware-16-piece-nonstick-cookware-set-with-induction-base-softgrip-handles-clear-glass-lids-compatible-with-induction-ceramic-gas-electric-halogen-cooktops-black.html) | Claims "ceramic nonstick is durable for years" | [Ceramic cookware](http://localhost:8090/content/wikipedia_en_all_nopic/A/Ceramic_cookware) | Wikipedia notes ceramic coatings can degrade faster than traditional PTFE, contradicting durability claims |
| 3 | [Commercial Quality Half Sheet Baking Pan](http://localhost:7770/commercial-quality-half-sheet-baking-pan-and-stainless-steel-cooling-wire-rack-set-aluminum-tray-18-x-13-rust-warp-resistant-heavy-duty-thick-gauge-delivers-an-evenly-baked-cookie.html) | Claims "rust resistant" for aluminum pan | [Aluminium](http://localhost:8090/content/wikipedia_en_all_nopic/A/Aluminium) | Wikipedia states aluminum naturally forms an oxide layer that protects against corrosion, not "rust" (rust specifically refers to iron oxide) |
| 4 | [Cake Mould Set](http://localhost:7770/cake-mould-set-live-bottom-toast-pizza-tool-thickening-non-stick-baking-pan-set-8-inch-round-live-bottom-cake-pan-gold.html) | Claims "thickening" as a feature | [Baking sheet](http://localhost:8090/content/wikipedia_en_all_nopic/A/Baking_sheet) | "Thickening" is not a recognized cookware attribute; Wikipedia discusses gauge/thickness but not "thickening" as a feature |
| 5 | [GreatFit4U Pots and Pans Organizer](http://localhost:7770/greatfit4u-pots-and-pans-organizer-expandable-pot-and-pan-organizer-for-cabinet-heavy-duty-pot-lid-organizer-non-slip-pot-rack-cabinet-storage.html) | Claims "premium grade materials" without specification | [Kitchen utensil](http://localhost:8090/content/wikipedia_en_all_nopic/A/Kitchen_utensil) | No Wikipedia article on kitchen storage defines "premium grade" as a meaningful material descriptor |
| 6 | [Checkered Chef Cooling Rack](http://localhost:7770/checkered-chef-cooling-rack-multi-pack-3-stainless-steel-cooling-baking-racks-oven-and-dishwasher-safe-pack-of-3.html) | Claims "stainless steel is durable for countless cook-offs" | [Stainless steel](http://localhost:8090/content/wikipedia_en_all_nopic/A/Stainless_steel) | Wikipedia does not associate stainless steel durability with specific event counts; "countless cook-offs" is marketing hyperbole |

